public abstract class Descriptor<T extends Describable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object

Metadata about a configurable instance.

Descriptor is an object that has metadata about a Describable object, and also serves as a factory (in a way this relationship is similar to Object/Class relationship. A Descriptor/Describable combination is used throughout in Hudson to implement a configuration/extensibility mechanism.

For example, Take the CVS support as an example, which is implemented in CVSSCM class. Whenever a job is configured with CVS, a new CVSSCM instance is created with the per-job configuration information. This instance gets serialized to XML, and this instance will be called to perform CVS operations for that job. This is the job of Describable — each instance represents a specific configuration of the CVS support (branch, CVSROOT, etc.)

For Hudson to create such configured CVSSCM instance, Hudson needs another object that captures the metadata of CVSSCM, and that is what a Descriptor is for. CVSSCM class has a singleton descriptor, and this descriptor helps render the configuration form, remember system-wide configuration (such as where cvs.exe is), and works as a factory.

Descriptor also usually have its associated views.

Persistence

Descriptor can persist data just by storing them in fields. However, it is the responsibility of the derived type to properly invoke save() and load().

Author:
Kohsuke Kawaguchi

newInstance

public T newInstance(org.kohsuke.stapler.StaplerRequest req,
                     net.sf.json.JSONObject formData)
                                     throws Descriptor.FormException
Creates a configured instance from the submitted form.

Hudson only invokes this method when the user wants an instance of T. So there's no need to check that in the implementation.

Parameters:
req - Always non-null. This object includes represents the entire submisison.
formData - The JSON object that captures the configuration data for this Descriptor. See http://hudson.gotdns.com/wiki/display/HUDSON/Structured+Form+Submission
Throws:
Descriptor.FormException - Signals a problem in the submitted form.
Since:
1.145

getHelpFile

public java.lang.String getHelpFile()
Returns the resource path to the help screen HTML, if any.

This value is relative to the context root of Hudson, so normally the values are something like "/plugin/emma/help.html" to refer to static resource files in a plugin, or "/publisher/EmmaPublisher/abc" to refer to Jelly script abc.jelly or a method EmmaPublisher.doAbc().

Returns:
null to indicate that there's no help.

Parameters:
